Merit awards are primarily made on the basis of student academic achievement.
column7: These awards of financial aid are posted to individual student accounts receivable.
column8: Institutionally provided student financial aid is credited to internal student accounts receivable balances and is funded primarily through the institutional budget as discounts to tuition and student fees, through restricted gifts or the allocated investment income of endowment funds. Merit awards are made on the basis of student academic achievement, leadership and individual talent. Awards made on the basis of financial need are determined from information submitted on the FAFSA (Free Application for Federal Student Assistance) form.
